label: St. Gallen, Stiftsbibliothek, Cod. Sang. 864

metadata.label: Title (English)
metadata.value: Composite manuscript containing works of Horace, Lucan, Sallust, and Ovid

metadata.label: Summary (English)
metadata.value: This codex consists of four independently produced parts, probably not written in St. Gall: 1. Horace, Odae (incomplete at the end, with some glosses); 2. Lucan, Pharsalia (incomplete at the end, heavily glossed; 3. Sallust, De coniuratione Catilinae (complete) and De bello Iugurthino (with some chapters missing); 4. Ovid, Amores (incomplete at the end, heavily glossed) and a page from the Metamorphoseon.

metadata.label: Persons
metadata.value: Author: Horatius Flaccus, Quintus; Author: Lucanus, Marcus Annaeus; Author: Ovidius Naso, Publius; Author: Sallustius Crispus, Gaius
